                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$275 - $400</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">5+ BR / 3,000+ sq ft</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$200 - $350</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$350 - $550</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <!-- RECURRING DISCOUNTS -->
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">
          Recurring Service Discounts in Florence
        </h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Most cleaning companies offer discounts for recurring service. Here's
          the typical structure you'll find in the Florence market:
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
          <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-gray-100">
                <th class="p-4 border border-gray-200 font-bold">Frequency</th>
                <th class="p-4 border border-gray-200 font-bold"
                  >Typical Discount</th
                >
                <th class="p-4 border border-gray-200 font-bold"
                  >3BR Home Example</th
                >
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Weekly</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">15-20% off</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$100 - $140/visit</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Bi-Weekly</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">10-15% off</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$115 - $160/visit</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Monthly</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">5-10% off</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$120 - $170/visit</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">One-Time</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Full price</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$125 - $175/visit</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          The discounts make sense for both parties. Recurring clients provide
          predictable revenue, and their homes stay cleaner between visits so
          each cleaning takes less time. It's a win-win.
        </p>

        <!-- FLORENCE VS OTHER MARKETS -->
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">
          How Florence Compares to Other Markets
        </h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          The Shoals area generally has lower cleaning prices than larger
          Alabama metros. Here's how Florence stacks up:
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
          <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-gray-100">
                <th class="p-4 border border-gray-200 font-bold">Market</th>
                <th class="p-4 border border-gray-200 font-bold"
                  >Standard (3BR)</th
                >
                <th class="p-4 border border-gray-200 font-bold"
                  >vs. Florence</th
                >
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="bg-[#FFA985]/10">
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200 font-bold"
                  >Florence/Shoals</td
                >
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$125 - $175</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">—</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Huntsville</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$135 - $200</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">+10-15%</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Birmingham</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$135 - $200</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">+10-15%</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">Nashville</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">$150 - $225</td>
                <td class="p-4 border border-gray-200">+20-30%</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <!-- RED FLAGS -->
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">
          Red Flags: Prices That Are Too Low
        </h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          If someone offers to clean your 3-bedroom Florence home for $50-60, be
          skeptical.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Here's the math: A thorough cleaning takes 2-4 hours minimum. At $50,
          that's barely minimum wage before supplies, travel, and any overhead.
          Nobody good works for that rate long-term.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          Suspiciously low prices typically mean: they'll rush through in 45
          minutes, they don't carry insurance (huge liability for you), they're
          cutting corners on products, or they won't be around next month.
        </p>

        <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">
          Frequently Asked Questions
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              How much does house cleaning cost in Florence, AL?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              Standard house cleaning in Florence costs $125-$175 for a typical
              3-bedroom home. Deep cleaning runs $200-$300, and move-out
              cleaning costs $250-$400. Florence pricing is about 10-15% lower
              than Huntsville or Birmingham.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              Why is house cleaning cheaper in Florence than Huntsville?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              The Shoals area has a lower cost of living than Huntsville, which
              affects service pricing across the board. This doesn't mean lower
              quality—reputable companies maintain the same standards in all
              markets they serve.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              How much do recurring cleaning services cost in Florence?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              Recurring cleaning offers 10-20% savings over one-time pricing.
              For a 3-bedroom home in Florence: weekly service averages
              $100-$140/visit, bi-weekly runs $115-$160/visit, and monthly costs
              $120-$170/visit.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              What affects the price of house cleaning?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              The main factors are: home size (square footage and bedrooms),
              service type (standard vs. deep), current condition of the home,
              frequency of service, and any add-ons like inside refrigerator or
              oven cleaning.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              Is it cheaper to hire an independent cleaner?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-0">
              Independent cleaners may charge $20-40 less per cleaning, but many
              lack insurance and bonding. If they damage something or get
              injured in your home, you could be liable. Professional companies
              cost slightly more but provide protection, consistency, and
              reliability.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- OUR PRICING -->
